# Setup New Web Project

This workflow automates the initialization of a high-quality web project.

1.  Ask the user for the project name.
    <!-- // turbo -->
2.  Create the project directory.
    <!-- // turbo -->
3.  Initialize project with `create-next-app` or `vite`.
    ```bash
    # Example logic - effectively pseudocode for the agent to execute
    # Run the interactive setup or use flags for defaults
    npx create-next-app@latest ./ --typescript --tailwind --eslint
    ```
4.  Install additional robust dependencies.
    ```bash
    npm install zod clsx tailwind-merge lucide-react
    ```
5.  Create a standard folder structure if not present.
    ```bash
    mkdir -p src/components src/lib src/hooks
    ```
